divs: Sighting Detailsat around 7:56 pm, I took pictures of the moon in an automatic setting instead of manual, by accident. I used a tripod to minimize shaking. I saw nothing with the naked eye, and did not see the object while I was taking the photos. I realized the pictures were no good, but put them on the computer anyway. there seems to be a star like object in the upper left quadrant of the photo. it appears to change shape in each picture. I am unable to identify it.
trends: There has been one other sighting in Atlantic Highlands
There were no other sightings in Atlantic Highlands on or around July 15th 2013
Summary: upon viewing my failure at trying to photograph the moon, i discovered a bright "star" in the upper left quadrant of the picture, when i lodaded the photos onto my computer.
